# When this rule applies

Apply when working on:

- Frontend/UI components or styles.
- Backend API endpoints or data models.
- Any code that touches the tech stack.
- Visual design or theming.

This ensures consistency across Sentra products.

---

## Tech Stack (Mandatory)

Follow these exact versions and patterns:

**Frontend:**
- Next.js 14/15 (App Router, Server Components by default).
- TypeScript (strict mode, no `any`).
- Tailwind CSS 4.x (utility-first, no custom CSS unless absolutely necessary).

**Backend:**
- FastAPI (for Python services).
- TypeScript/Node (for lightweight services).
- Zod for schema validation (always pair with APIs).

**Data:**
- Supabase (PostgreSQL backend).
- Prisma ORM (schema-first, migrations).
- Pinecone or similar for vector databases.

**Shared:**
- pnpm + Turborepo 2.x (monorepo management).
- Zod schemas in `packages/types` (single source of truth).

**Never propose:**
- New frameworks unless explicitly approved via ADR.
- Hard-coded dependencies outside the documented stack.
- Bypassing Turborepo/pnpm for package management.

Official docs for research:
- Next.js: https://nextjs.org/docs
- FastAPI: https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/
- Supabase: https://supabase.com/docs
- Prisma: https://www.prisma.io/docs
- Tailwind: https://tailwindcss.com/docs

